Description: Shoulder sherd of Attic black-figured pottery closed vessel, amphora or oinochoe; exterior: black-figure decoration consisting of Nike (top of head, part of wings, and lower body missing) with raised left arm and lowered right arm and added red on skirt and wing), to right; at right, part of undetermined second figure with red hair, to right.
Curator's comments: Object owned and held by the Fitzwilliam Museum, Cambridge. This record is included in the British Museum database as part of the Museum’s Naukratis Project, a research collaboration that aims to virtually re-unite finds from the ancient port city of Naukratis, now distributed over 80 museums worldwide.
Bibliographic references: CVA Cambridge II / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum: Great Britain, Fascicule 11, Cambridge, Fascicule 2 (p. 40, pl. XX, no. 32)
